ntry when we keep on pushing the messages of miracles, signs and wonders.', 3800, 0), (394073, 'That boy shakes me upside down and inside out.', 6803, 0), (394074, 'His green-flecked brown eyes twinkle, and we laugh together, easy and light. He opens the door for me, and I say goodbye, floating over to where my family waits in our Winnebago. And I can''t tell you if my feet actually touch the ground, because at this very moment, this Bird, well, she flies.', 6803, 0), (394075, 'In our opinion, Coke is great from a can, still good from a bottle, yet hard to get just right from the fountain. But oh, when they do get it right, it tastes good enough to be an eighth wonder of the world.', 6803, 0), (394076, 'Do you remember a time when men were men? When they would do anything for love, for their friends or for their country?''No, I don''t, but at least I would love to read about those men!', 1213, 0), (394077, 'South Africa is the only country where an overwhelming majority in complete political control is apparently so threatened by a tiny minority that they need racist affirmative action policies to protect the majority by legislatively excluding the minority totally from the job market.', 11026, 0), (394078, 'I am not Nigerian because I was born in Nigeria but because Nigeria was born in me.', 11016, 0), (394079, 'Events went on to show that it is not by chance that a prime minister reaches such lofty heights and that, as the infallible wisdom of nations has demonstrated time and time again, each country gets the government it deserves, although it must be said that while it is true to say that prime ministers, for good or ill, are not all the same, it is no less true to say, are all countries.', 1357, 0), (394080, 'My country can never be taken away from me now', 62027, 0), (394081, 'What kind of country has this become? Decent people can’t do anything without being watched.', 11107, 0), (394082, 'If half of a country is rotten, the other half will soon start rottin