as always been to hold my own with whatever''s going. Not against: with.', 35, 0), (395479, 'There is no quality of human nature so nearly royal as the ability to yield gracefully.', 62221, 0), (395480, 'The best thing we can do is to make wherever we''re lost look as much like home as we can.', 10583, 0), (395481, 'Make a virtue of necessity.', 12764, 0), (395482, 'Cooperation is doing with a smile what you have to do anyhow.', 33, 0), (395483, 'We must make the best of those ills which cannot be avoided.', 16733, 0), (395484, 'For so must it be  and help me do my part.', 33, 0), (395485, 'There are no conditions to which a man cannot become accustomed.', 93, 0), (395486, 'A private railroad car is not an acquired taste. One takes to it immediately.', 62222, 0), (395487, 'Man adapts himself to everything  to the best and the worst.', 2800, 0), (395488, 'Being unready and ill-equipped is what you have to expect in life. It is the universal predicament. It is your lot as a human being to lack what it takes. Circumstances are seldom right. You never have the capacities  the strength  the wisdom  the virtue you ought to have. You must always do with less than you need in a situation vastly different from what you would have chosen as appropriate for your special endowments.', 62223, 0), (395489, 'In the face of an obstacle which is impossible to overcome  stubbornness is stupid.', 477, 0), (395490, 'Very few live by choice. Every man is placed in his present condition by causes which acted without his foresight  and with which he did not always willingly cooperate  and therefore you will rarely meet one who does not think the lot of his neighbor better than his own.', 2087, 0), (395491, 'To exist is to adapt  and if one could not adapt  one died and made room for those who could.', 1682, 0), (395492, 'Happy the man who early learns the wide chasm that lies between his wishes and his powers.', 62224, 0), (395493, 'Real life is  to most men ... a perpetual compromise between the ideal and the possible.', 95, 0), (395494, 'People are lucky and unlucky ... according to the ratio between what they get and what they have been led to expect.', 4111, 0), (395495, 'He who cannot do what he wants must make do with what he can.', 21159, 0), (395496, 'What has always made a hell on earth has been that man has tried to make it his heaven.', 8753, 0), (395497, 'Good is not good  where better is expected.', 1348, 0), (395498, 'Nobody has things just as he would like them. The thing to do is to make a success with what material I have. It is a sheer waste of time and soul-power to imagine what I would do if things were different. They are not different.', 62225, 0), (395499, 'We must like what we have when we don''t have what we like.', 62226, 0), (395500, 'Better is the enemy of the good.', 808, 0);
