int... is to dwell upon the brightest parts in every prospect  to call off the thoughts when turning upon disagreeable objects  and strive to be pleased with the present circumstances.', 62233, 0), (395531, 'Everything has its wonders  even darkness and silence  and I learn  whatever state I may be in  therein to be content.', 701, 0), (395532, 'Life is not always what one wants it to be  but to make the best of it  as it is  is the only way of being happy.', 62234, 0), (395533, 'The English know how to make the best of things. Their so-called muddling through is simply skill at dealing with the inevitable.', 3621, 0), (395534, 'I make the most of all that comes and the least of all that goes.', 297, 0), (395535, 'We cannot conquer fate and necessity  yet we can yield to them in such a manner as to be greater than if we could.', 8764, 0), (395536, 'The idea came to me that I was  am  and will be  but perhaps will not become. This did not scare me. There was for me in being an intensity I did not feel in becoming.', 62235, 0), (395537, 'Here is a rule to remember when anything tempts you to feel bitter: not  "This is a misfortune " but "To bear this worthily is good fortune."', 267, 0), (395538, 'There is no good in arguing with the inevitable. The only argument available with an east wind is to put on your overcoat.', 1247, 0), (395539, 'Trouble will come soon enough  and when he does come receive him as pleasantly as possible ... the more amiably you greet him  the sooner he will go away.', 39771, 0), (395540, 'Adapt yourself to the things among which your lot has been cast and love sincerely the fellow creatures with whom destiny has ordained that you shall live.', 267, 0), (395541, 'When we accept tough jobs as a challenge to our ability and wade into them with joy and enthusiasm  miracles can happen.', 62236, 0), (395542, 'Love only what befalls you and is spun for you by fate.', 267, 0), (395543, 'What you can''t get out of  get into wholeheartedly.', 1932, 0),