r.', 37762, 0), (395831, 'If you can react the same way to winning and losing  that''s a big accomplishment. That quality is important because it stays with you the rest of your life.', 62310, 0), (395832, 'You have striven so hard  and so long  to compel life. Can''t you now slowly change  and let life slowly drift into you ... let the invisible life steal into you and slowly possess you.', 178, 0), (395833, 'Coercive power is the curse of the universe  coactive power  the enrichment and advancement of every human soul.', 62311, 0), (395834, 'I began to have an idea of my life  not as the slow shaping of achievement to fit my preconceived purposes  but as the gradual discovery and growth of a purpose which I did not know.', 12468, 0), (395835, 'A guru might say that spiritual deepening involves a journey toward the unselfconscious living of life as it unfolds  rather than toward a willful determination to make it happen.', 62312, 0), (395836, 'Events that are predestined require but little management. They manage themselves. They slip into place while we sleep  and suddenly we are aware that the thing we fear to attempt  is already accomplished.', 62313, 0), (395837, 'O golden Silence  bid our souls be still  and on the foolish fretting of our care lay thy soft touch of healing unaware!', 62314, 0), (395838, 'Stress is basically a disconnection from the earth  a forgetting of the breath. Stress is an ignorant state. It believes that everything is an emergency. Nothing is that important. Just lie down.', 3767, 0), (395839, 'When you learn not to want things so badly  life comes to you.', 62315, 0), (395840, 'No day is so bad it can''t be fixed with a nap.', 62316, 0), (395841, 'Believe there is a great power silently working all things for good  behave yourself and never mind the rest.', 1766, 0), (395842, 'One by one the sands are flowing  One by one the moments fall  Some are coming  some are going  Do not strive to grasp them all.', 62317, 0), (395843, 'Somehow  