ence develops some latent force within you  you will grow vigorous and happy  however adverse your circumstances may seem to be.', 41914, 0), (395984, 'Necessity is often the spur to genius.', 143, 0), (395985, 'Necessity is the mother of "taking chances."', 286, 0), (395986, 'Necessity makes even the timid brave.', 4812, 0), (395987, 'People wish to be settled  only as far as they are unsettled is there any hope for them.', 760, 0), (395988, 'Difficulties are meant to rouse  not discourage. The human spirit is to grow strong by conflict.', 3573, 0), (395989, 'Adversity causes some men to break  others to break records.', 62349, 0), (395990, 'I think there is this about the great troubles - they teach us the art of cheerfulness  whereas the small ones cultivate the industry of discontent.', 62350, 0), (395991, 'Opposition inflames the enthusiast  never converts him.', 62240, 0), (395992, 'The thought that we are enduring the unendurable is one of the things that keeps us going.', 18173, 0), (395993, 'If you do things well  do them better. Be daring  be first  be different  be just.', 2132, 0), (395994, 'A certain amount of opposition is a great help to a man  it is what he wants and must have to be good for anything. Hardship and opposition are the native soil of manhood and self-reliance.', 62351, 0), (395995, 'Difficulties  opposition  criticism -  these things are meant to be overcome  and there is a special joy in facing them and in coming out on top. It is only when there is nothing but praise that life loses its charm and I begin to wonder what I should do about it.', 62352, 0), (395996, 'They sicken of calm  who know the storm.', 201, 0), (395997, 'Without the burden of afflictions it is impossible to reach the height of grace. The gift of grace increases as the struggles increase.', 62353, 0), (395998, 'When the going gets tough  the tough get going.', 62354, 0), (395999, 'The effects of opposition are wonderful. There are men who rise refreshed on hearing of a threat  men to whom a crises  which intimidates and paralyzes the majority  comes as graceful and beloved as a bride!', 760, 0), (396000, 'Remember that the Devil doesn''t sleep  but seeks our ruin in a thousand different ways', 62355, 0);
